metadata.name: Study One: Design and Forms #25
metadata.description:
Design and Form, a fundamental course at the Bauhaus, played a pivotal role in shaping the renowned art school's unique approach to design education. Founded in 1919 by architect Walter Gropius, the Bauhaus sought to bridge the gap between art and industry, promoting the idea that design should be both functional and aesthetically pleasing. The Design and Form course served as a cornerstone of this philosophy, providing students with a comprehensive understanding of the principles and techniques that underpin all forms of visual expression.

At the heart of the Design and Form course was the exploration of the fundamental elements of design, such as line, shape, color, and texture. Students were encouraged to experiment with these elements through hands-on exercises, engaging in a process of discovery and self-expression. The course emphasized the importance of developing a keen sense of observation and a deep understanding of materials, enabling students to create harmonious compositions that seamlessly blended form and function.

One of the distinguishing features of the Design and Form course was its interdisciplinary nature. The Bauhaus believed that design should transcend traditional boundaries, and students from various disciplines, including painting, sculpture, architecture, and crafts, came together to learn and collaborate. This interdisciplinary approach fostered a rich exchange of ideas, inspiring students to push the boundaries of their respective fields and embrace new ways of thinking. The Design and Form course at the Bauhaus laid the foundation for the school's revolutionary approach to design education, leaving an indelible mark on the world of art and design.

-	Hit s for svg export
-	Hit p for png export

Params for palette, form factor, mode and composition seed 

Feature overrides mode to give you a rare gold or purple

metadata.description:
The mountains account for 70% of Taiwan's land area and are so dense that they are known as the "Island of Mountains".
moreover,only 1% of the world's forests can be called fog forests, and Taiwan is among them.
due to regional differences in climate, geological history and phytogeography,the mountain forests have a high diversity of plants and animals,which attracts many climbers to make the trip.

山岳總面積佔據了臺灣土地面積70%，高山密度之高，足以譽為「群山之島」。
不僅如此，全世界只有1%的森林可以稱之為霧林，台灣也在其中。
由於區域氣候的差異，以及地質史及植物地理學的因素,
山地霧林擁有極高的植物及動物的多樣性，更是吸引無數爬山愛好者前來觀光。

metadata.name: 🌶️ HOT PEPPER GANG 🌶️ #59
metadata.description:
Say hello to the 🌶️ HOT PEPPER GANG 🌶️ 

The 🌶️ HOT PEPPER GANG 🌶️ is a profile picture project by FILTER8 released under his alias Drawvolution for the PICANTE Community Event on Tezos.

Picante is the Spanish word for Spicy. So what's Hot & Spicy? Right a hot pepper. 

FILTER8 challenged himself with releasing a 8x8 px 🌶️ embedded on a 24x24 px background to give the 🌶️  more room. The 🌶️ consists of 5 Layers: Location (3), Pulp (20), Personality (9), Mouth (7), Crown (10). He used his signatures Win95 retro color palette of 16 colors to design the artworks.  

🎁 BONUS: After the mint the top 5 🌶️ HOT PEPPER GANG 🌶️ Collectors will get one of their PFP airdropped as a 8x8 on-chain version on 8bidou, the on-chain pixel marketplace on Tezos.


👉 Join the the 🌶️ HOT PEPPER GANG 🌶️ and get spicy 


🌶️ Hot Pepper Size 8x8 px
🌶️ Canvas Size: 24x24 pixel
🌶️ Format: .png
🌶️ Layers: 5
🌶️ Traits: 46
🌶️ One 8x8 on-chain HOT PEPPER Version included for the 5 top collectors.

🌶️ Thanks to PureSpider for this spicy code.

metadata.name: (fx)moji #124
metadata.description:
Emoji is the word for visual language, a way to express emotion without words.

From its humble origins as a Japanese emoticon in the mid-1990s, they exploded in popularity when appeared as a critical part of Apple's iPhone launch in 2007. The internationalization of emoji is an inexorable force, and today it is almost impossible to send a message without using one.

Emojis evolved as a way to communicate quickly and easily, and now they will evolve one more time and become an NFT generative art reborn as (fx)moji where basic geometric forms create a new full set of emojis expressions.

32 emojis,
7 Animations,
6 Color &
Infinite expressions 😊

Made with love ❤️ 🧡 💛 💚 💙 and p5js

metadata.name: MOMENT #123
metadata.description:
An endless row of them making up each life. Some poignant, some inspiring, some grievous, some affirming - but most of them a tad boring, a bit generic, almost forgettable like bland fabric. How can a life constructed from such mundanity count for anything? Maybe thanks to the last one, the one that stitches them all together, like a punchline to an absurdist joke.

Generative art written in JavaScript + Canvas with a little bit of help from p5.js.

metadata.name: Geode #18
metadata.description:
A single seed shape is chosen from 13, and placed onto the plane. At every step, a copy of this seed is laid edge-to-edge adjacent to an existing shape, without causing any overlaps. This copy is colored based on the edge it shares with the existing shape. The process continues until the animation completes.

New shapes are placed closest to a moving target. In some mints, this target is slow moving, causing new shapes to expand radially from the seed. In other mints, this target races around, causing new shapes to chase it. 

Each of the 13 shapes forms different patterns under different circumstances. Not all patterns will be explored.

Controls:
  - SPACE: Pause/unpause the animation.
  - ENTER: Skip the animation.
  - R: Restart the animation.

URL Params:
  - "preview=1": Skip the animation.
  - "flex=1": Adapt the boundaries to the size of the window.
  - “slow=1”: Draw only one shape per frame.
